OL,6,FThis notwithstanding, the ASA said
OL,7,Fthey, "considered the emphasis on a
OL,8,Fchase, and the speed inherent to that,
OL,9,Fand the driving manoeuvres featured
OL,10,Fwould be dangerous and irresponsible
OL,11,Fif emulated in real life on a public
OL,12,Fhighway."
OL,14,FIn its ruling, the ASA said the ad
OL,15,Fcould not be broadcast in the UK in
OL,16,Fits current form and that it told Mars
OL,17,FWrigley Confectionery UK Ltd not to
OL,18,Fcondone or encourage irresponsible
OL,19,Fdriving that was likely to breach the
OL,20,Flegal requirements of the Highway Code.
